definitions.definition: A type of shoe with an inflexible , often wooden sole sometimes with an open heel .
examples: Dutch people rarely wear clogs these days.
The plumber cleared the clog from the drain.

definitions.definition: A weight, such as a log or block of wood, attached to a person or animal to hinder motion.
That which hinders or impedes motion; an encumbrance , restraint , or impediment of any kind.
